   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | data | | datalen |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The contents of data depends on the type and are described below. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DEVINFO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Structure for device information
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It must be saved before the devid is used.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If devid is 0, it indicates the vital recorder itself (for example, filter-generated tracks,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: event markers)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A new DEVINFO can appear for the same device id (devid) in a file. In this case, the new value
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should overwrites the previous value.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: devid and trkid are meaningful only within the same file.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Even if the program instance is different, the Vital Recorder is implemented with the same devid
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: value if the same kind of equipment is connected to the same physical port.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,476:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For example, if two BIS devices are connected to COM5 and COM6, the previous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: devid remains the same even if the program is terminated and then re-executed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (save the devid to the registry)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,480:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If you intentionally terminate the program and then switch between the two BIS
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: devices and run the program again, the devids may cross each other.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Name | Type | Length | Description |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|------|--------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | devid | DWORD | 4 | device identifier |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: typename | string | 4+len | device type |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | devname | string | 4+len | device name |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | port | string | 4+len | Information
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that allows device types such as COM1, COM10, ETH1, and Line Input Mixer to recognize the port to which the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device is connected with this information only. If the device type and port are the same, it is generally considered
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the same device. |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TRKINFO
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Structure for track information
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TRKINFO must be appeared before the first record with the track id.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Otherwise, the record should be ignored.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tracks are separated by trkids, which are 2-byte integers.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,528:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The numeric value of trkid itself has no meaning and there is no continuity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trkids can be changed every time the program is executed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The order of the tracks is not in the order of trkid size, but in the order of appearance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and the CMD
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ORDER command described later.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tracks with a devid of 0 (vital recorder itself) and name of EVENT are treated specially in the vital
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recorder. It is not displayed on a separate track but displayed in the event bar.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Name | Type | Length | Description |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|------|--------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | trkid | WORD | 2 | track id |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | rec
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: type | BYTE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 1 | TYPE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WAV = 1, TYPE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NUM = 2, TYPE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STR = 5 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | recfmt | BYTE | 1 | FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: NULL = 0 (for TYPE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: STR),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FLOAT = 1, FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOUBLE = 2, FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CHAR = 3, FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BYTE = 4, FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SHORT = 5, FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WORD = 6,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LONG = 7, FMT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DWORD = 8 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | name | string | 4+len | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | unit | string | 4+len | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | minval | float | 4 | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | maxval |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: float | 4 | |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | color | color | 4 | 4byte ARGB format |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | srate | float | 4 | sample rate |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | adc
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: gain | double | 8 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: measured_value = adc_offset + saved_value * adc_gain
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-21 16:19:19,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
